# Mission Control Design System

## Design Philosophy

Mission Control is an **institutional-grade trading dashboard**. Every design decision should communicate:
- **Precision** - Financial data demands accuracy
- **Confidence** - Users trust this system with real money
- **Clarity** - Complex metrics made instantly understandable
- **Professionalism** - Hedge fund quality, not retail trading app

## Typography

### Font Stack
```css
--font-display: 'Playfair Display', serif;  /* Headers, large numbers */
--font-body: 'Inter', sans-serif;            /* Body text, UI */
--font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;    /* Prices, codes, data */
```

### Hierarchy
- **H1 (Dashboard titles)**: 48px (3rem), Playfair Display, font-bold
- **H2 (Section headers)**: 12px (0.75rem), Inter, font-semibold, uppercase, tracking-wider
- **Metrics (large)**: 36-48px (2.25-3rem), Playfair Display, font-bold
- **Body text**: 14px (0.875rem), Inter, leading-relaxed
- **Data/prices**: 14px (0.875rem), JetBrains Mono, font-mono

### Rules
- Use serif (Playfair) for **numbers and emotional impact** (P&L, account value)
- Use sans-serif (Inter) for **UI and readability** (labels, descriptions)
- Use monospace for **precision data** (prices, timestamps, codes)
- Never mix more than 2 font families on a single page

## Color System

### Semantic Colors
```css
/* Profit/Loss */
--profit: #16a34a;      /* green-600 */
--loss: #dc2626;        /* red-600 */

/* Positions */
--long: #22c55e;        /* green-500 */
--short: #ef4444;       /* red-500 */

/* Neutrals */
--slate-900: #0f172a;   /* Primary text */
--stone-600: #57534e;   /* Secondary text */
--stone-400: #a8a29e;   /* Tertiary text */
--stone-200: #e7e5e4;   /* Borders */
--stone-50: #fafaf9;    /* Background */

/* Accents */
--sky-600: #0284c7;     /* Primary actions */
--orange-500: #f97316;  /* Warnings */
--blue-500: #3b82f6;    /* Info */
```

### Color Rules
- **Green = profit/long**, **Red = loss/short** (universal convention)
- Use **stone** palette for neutrals (warmer than gray, more sophisticated)
- Use **slate-900** for primary text (not pure black)
- Borders: `border-stone-200` (subtle, not harsh)
- Backgrounds: `bg-stone-50` (off-white, reduces eye strain)

### Contrast Requirements
- All text must meet WCAG 2.2 AA: 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text
- Interactive elements: 3:1 contrast with surroundings
- Focus states: 3:1 contrast, visible outline

## Layout & Spacing

### Grid System
```tsx
/* Dashboard layout */
<div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 py-12">  {/* Standard container */}
  <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
    {/* Metric cards */}
  </div>
</div>

/* Institutional dashboard (wider) */
<div className="max-w-[1600px] mx-auto px-8 py-12">
  {/* More data, needs more space */}
</div>
```

### Spacing Scale
- **gap-3**: 12px - Tight groups (badges, chips)
- **gap-4**: 16px - Related items (nav buttons)
- **gap-6**: 24px - Cards, sections
- **gap-8**: 32px - Major sections
- **mb-12**: 48px - Section breaks
- **mb-16**: 64px - Page sections

### Card Design
```tsx
<div className="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
  {/* Content */}
</div>
```

**Rules:**
- White background (`bg-white`)
- Subtle border (`border-stone-200`)
- Rounded corners (`rounded-xl` = 12px)
- Generous padding (`p-6` = 24px minimum)
- Hover effects for interactive cards
- Never use drop shadows by default (only on hover)

## Components

### Metric Cards
```tsx
<div className="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-6">
  <div className="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-500 mb-2">
    {label}
  </div>
  <div className="font-serif text-4xl font-bold text-sky-600">
    {value}
  </div>
  {subtitle && <div className="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-2">{subtitle}</div>}
</div>
```

### Data Tables
```tsx
<table className="w-full text-sm">
  <thead className="border-b border-stone-200">
    <tr>
      <th className="text-left py-3 px-2 font-semibold text-stone-600">Header</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr className="border-b border-stone-100 hover:bg-stone-50">
      <td className="py-3 px-2 text-stone-900">Data</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
```

**Rules:**
- Text size: `text-sm` (14px)
- Header: `font-semibold text-stone-600`
- Borders: `border-stone-200` (header), `border-stone-100` (rows)
- Hover: `hover:bg-stone-50`
- Padding: `py-3 px-2` (vertical 12px, horizontal 8px)

### Badges
```tsx
/* Side indicator */
<span className="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-semibold bg-green-100 text-green-700">
  LONG
</span>

/* Status indicator */
<span className="px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold bg-blue-100 text-blue-700">
  OPEN
</span>
```

**Rules:**
- Use `rounded` for categories (side, type)
- Use `rounded-full` for status (open, closed, pending)
- Always pair background + text color (e.g., `bg-green-100 text-green-700`)

### Alerts
```tsx
<div className="rounded-xl p-4 bg-red-50 border border-red-200">
  <div className="flex items-start gap-3">
    <div className="text-red-600">⚠️</div>
    <div>
      <div className="font-semibold text-sm text-red-900">{message}</div>
      <div className="text-xs text-red-700 mt-1">{details}</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

**Severity levels:**
- **Critical**: `bg-red-50 border-red-200 text-red-900`
- **Warning**: `bg-orange-50 border-orange-200 text-orange-900`
- **Info**: `bg-blue-50 border-blue-200 text-blue-900`

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.2 AA Baseline)

### Required
- ✅ All interactive elements have visible focus states
- ✅ Color is never the only indicator (use icons + text)
- ✅ All images have descriptive alt text
- ✅ Semantic HTML (`<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<table>`)
- ✅ Keyboard navigation works for all interactions
- ✅ Form inputs have associated labels
- ✅ Sufficient color contrast (4.5:1 text, 3:1 UI)

### Focus States
```tsx
className="focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-slate-400 focus:ring-offset-2"
```

### Skip Links (for complex dashboards)
```tsx
<a href="#main-content" className="sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:absolute focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-50 focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:bg-white focus:border focus:border-stone-200">
  Skip to main content
</a>
```

## Data Visualization

### Charts
- Use **canvas** for performance (not SVG for large datasets)
- Color blind safe: Use patterns + colors
- Always label axes and provide legends
- Show data points on hover
- Include "last updated" timestamp

### Number Formatting
```tsx
// Currency
const formatCurrency = (value: number) => 
  new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', {
    style: 'currency',
    currency: 'USD',
    minimumFractionDigits: 0,
    maximumFractionDigits: 0,
  }).format(value);

// Percentage
const formatPercent = (value: number) => 
  `${value >= 0 ? '+' : ''}${value.toFixed(2)}%`;

// Large numbers
const formatLarge = (value: number) => 
  value >= 1_000_000 ? `${(value / 1_000_000).toFixed(1)}M` :
  value >= 1_000 ? `${(value / 1_000).toFixed(1)}K` :
  value.toFixed(0);
```

**Rules:**
- Currency: No decimals for large amounts ($1,936,241 not $1,936,241.90)
- Percentages: Always show sign (+2.5% or -1.3%)
- Returns: 2 decimal places (2.45%)
- Prices: 2 decimal places ($178.20)
- Large numbers: Use K/M suffixes in tight spaces

## Micro-Interactions

### Hover States
- Cards: `hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow`
- Buttons: `hover:bg-stone-200 transition-colors`
- Table rows: `hover:bg-stone-50`
- Links: `hover:text-stone-700`

### Loading States
```tsx
{loading && (
  <div className="min-h-screen bg-stone-50 flex items-center justify-center">
    <div className="text-stone-400">Loading...</div>
  </div>
)}
```

### Empty States
```tsx
{items.length === 0 && (
  <div className="text-center text-stone-400 py-8">
    No data available
  </div>
)}
```

## Voice & Tone

### Dashboard Copy
- **Headers**: Clear, descriptive ("Risk Metrics" not "Risks")
- **Labels**: Precise terminology ("Net Liquidation" not "Account Value")
- **Tooltips**: Explain calculations ("VaR (95%) - Maximum expected loss at 95% confidence")
- **Errors**: Helpful, actionable ("Dashboard snapshot not found. Run dashboard_data_aggregator.py first.")

### Tone Rules
- **Professional** but not stuffy
- **Precise** but not jargon-heavy
- **Confident** but include disclaimers
- **Direct** - No marketing fluff

### Examples
❌ "Your amazing portfolio is crushing it!"  
✅ "Portfolio up 2.3% today"

❌ "Uh oh, looks like you might have some risk!"  
✅ "Daily loss at 2.4% (limit: 3.0%)"

## Performance

### Optimization Rules
- Use `'use client'` only when needed (interactivity, hooks)
- Fetch data client-side for real-time updates
- Use `dynamic = 'force-dynamic'` for API routes
- Minimize bundle size (no heavy chart libraries for simple viz)
- Canvas > SVG for complex charts
- Lazy load heavy components

### Data Refresh
- Auto-refresh every 30 seconds for live data
- Show "last updated" timestamp
- Visual indicator when data is stale (>5 minutes old)
- Graceful degradation if API fails

## Error Handling

### API Errors
```tsx
if (error || !data) {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-stone-50 flex items-center justify-center">
      <div className="text-center">
        <div className="text-red-600 font-semibold mb-2">Error Loading Dashboard</div>
        <div className="text-stone-500 text-sm">{error}</div>
        <div className="text-stone-400 text-xs mt-4">
          Make sure dashboard_data_aggregator.py is running
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Validation Errors
- Show inline, near the problem
- Use red-50 background with red-600 text
- Provide actionable next steps
- Never blame the user

## Responsive Design

### Breakpoints
- **Mobile**: < 768px (single column, stacked cards)
- **Tablet**: 768px - 1024px (2 columns)
- **Desktop**: > 1024px (3-4 columns)
- **Large**: > 1600px (institutional dashboard, 5 columns)

### Mobile Considerations
- Tables scroll horizontally on mobile
- Metric cards stack vertically
- Navigation becomes hamburger menu (if needed)
- Touch targets: minimum 44x44px

## Animation

### Transitions
```css
transition-colors  /* 150ms - color changes */
transition-shadow  /* 150ms - elevation changes */
transition-all     /* 150ms - multiple properties */
```

### Rules
- Keep transitions under 200ms (feels instant)
- Use for hover states, not page loads
- Disable animations for `prefers-reduced-motion`

## Institutional Standards

### Data Integrity
- Always show data source ("From IBKR" or "Calculated")
- Include calculation methodology in tooltips
- Show confidence intervals for estimates
- Timestamp everything
- Log all system decisions (audit trail)

### Risk Communication
- Use color + text + icons (never color alone)
- Show thresholds clearly (e.g., "2.4% / 3.0% limit")
- Warnings appear before critical levels
- Critical alerts are dismissible but persistent

### Compliance
- Include disclaimers on all pages
- "Past performance does not guarantee future results"
- "Trading involves risk of loss"
- Mark paper trading accounts clearly

