## Don'ts

❌ **Never:**
- Use pure black (`#000`) or pure white (`#fff`) for text
- Use gradients on text (readability issues)
- Animate core metrics (distracting)
- Hide critical risk information
- Use marketing language ("crushing it!", "to the moon!")
- Show fake/demo data without clear labeling
- Use Comic Sans, Papyrus, or decorative fonts
- Center-align data tables (left-align for scannability)
- Use red/green for non-financial data (avoid overloading meaning)

## Testing Checklist

Before shipping any dashboard feature:

- [ ] Works with real IBKR data (not just mocks)
- [ ] Handles missing data gracefully
- [ ] Shows loading states
- [ ] Shows error states with helpful messages
- [ ] All numbers format correctly
- [ ] Color contrast meets WCAG AA
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works
- [ ] Responsive on mobile/tablet/desktop
- [ ] Data timestamps are visible
- [ ] Tooltips explain calculations
- [ ] No console errors
- [ ] Fast load time (<2s)

## When to Break the Rules

These rules ensure consistency, but break them when:
- **User safety** requires it (e.g., flashing red for critical alert)
- **Data clarity** demands it (e.g., larger font for critical metric)
- **Accessibility** needs it (e.g., higher contrast for specific use case)

Always document why you broke a rule in code comments.
